prompt: Summarize the following story in first person: Two months ago something very important happened. I fought back. I defied their rules and systematic behavior. My parents wanted to raise me to be super religious, but I wasn't feeling it. They insisted they wanted me to follow my own path. That was a commendable thing for them to do. But it certainly didn't stay that way. I thought they were going to be supportive of me, but then they do a complete reversal. They deliberately shut me out of their life. They went back on their word. The two people I thought I could trust, I couldn't trust anymore. I was disowned for not wanting to be manipulated into something I didn't believe in. I am in awe at the stance they took. They took belief in someone that wasn't their own child. Imagine not wanting to support your child.

choices.text: They thought I was going to be a puppet. They tried to force me into their way of thinking. I was a rebel, and I was going to be a rebel no matter what. I had to fight for what I believed in. I am so glad I did. I am so glad I didn't give in to their manipulation. I am so glad I stood up for myself. It was the best decision I ever made. I will never go back to that place. I will never let anyone manipulate me again.
